**A debounce function ensures a given function is only called after a specified delay has elapsed since its last invocation.**

```javascript
// Debounce function
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example usage: log input value only after user stops typing for 500ms
const input = document.querySelector('#myInput');
input.addEventListener('input', debounce(function(event) {
  console.log('Input value:', event.target.value);
}, 500));
```

**HTML for the example:**
```html
<input id="myInput" type="text" placeholder="Type here..." />
```
